On Wednesday, Mabuyakhulu made another brief appearance at the Durban Commercial Crimes Court. He is facing charges which include fraud and corruption.
During the appearance, Mabuyakhulu's legal representative Advocate Jimmy Howse revealed that the politician has already made a request for further particulars of the state's charges against him.AdChoicesADVERTISINGinRead invented by Teads

Howse said once these are received from the state Mabuyakhulu - who is charged alongside 15 others - intends approaching the head of the Special Crimes Court to have his trial separated from that of his co-accused.
Howse argued that a lengthy trial could be prejudicial to his client who only faces six charges out of a combined total of 77 charges faced by the others.


 







