The charges relate to R28 million which the KZN government forked out for a music concert - the North Sea Jazz Festival - that never took place.
The transaction took place in 2012 when Mabuyakhulu was the MEC for Economic Development, Tourism and Environmental Affairs.

Mabuyakhulu is accused of having pocketed R300 00 of that money.
The Mercury